-- 
Bank of America Receives Consent to Amend Some Hybrid Securities

-- B y   S t e v e   D i c k s o n
-- 
2011-12-08T13:26:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/bank-of-america-receives-consent-to-amend-some-hybrid-securities.html
Bank of America Corp. (BAC) , the second-
biggest U.S. bank by assets, received consent from investors to
amend the terms of certain preferred hybrid income term
securities, or HITS.  Holders of the securities agreed to the new terms, the
Charlotte, North Carolina-based company said today in a
statement. The company will pay $2.50 for each $1,000 in
liquidation. The total aggregate liquidation amount outstanding
was $1.55 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Steve Dickson in New York at 
 sdickson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scheer at 
 dscheer@bloomberg.net  